  title={IPP-HF: An Identity Privacy Protection Scheme for Consortium Blockchain Hyperledger Fabric}, 
  year={2022},
  volume={},
  number={},
  pages={1984-1989},
  abstract={The open and transparent ledger of blockchain makes the user’s identity and transaction details easily revealed in the blockchain network, and the privacy of individuals is seriously threatened, so the privacy protection issue gradually becomes a new challenge in blockchain. To solve the problem of identity privacy leakage during blockchain transactions, this paper proposes an identity privacy protection scheme based on the Hyperledger Fabric(IPP-HF). By making appropriate improvements to the certificateless signature and using the cooperation of long-term and short-term pseudo-identities, this paper designs an identity privacy protection scheme based on certificateless signature on the consortium blockchain Fabric, which makes the scheme satisfy the node identity anonymity and protects the privacy of user identity. Through theoretical analysis, it is proved that IPP-HF scheme can resist common public key replacement attacks and tampering attacks, and has the characteristics of signature unforgeability and guaranteed node anonymity. Finally, by comparing with other schemes, IPPHF scheme ensures high signature and verification efficiency while having strong anonymity.},
