  pages={2340-2347},
  abstract={Online Social Networks(OSNs) have grown in popularity along with the use of mobile devices and the advancement of network technologies. Every time we experience a wonderful moment in our daily lives, we feel the impulse to capture it on camera and share it on OSNs. Users are frequently hesitated or struggled while sharing photos because photos often contain some privacy. To address this problem, we propose the design, implementation, and evaluation of SmartCircles, a personalized policy recommendation scheme based on attribute analysis. SmartCircles acts as a plugin to existing photo sharing OSNs, and it enables the following: a)extract various factors when users upload their photos, b)calculate the intimacy of photos and users according to extracted factors, c)calculate profit and loss, and recommend optimal policy by trade-off them. We have implemented a prototype of SmartCircles, and evaluation results have demonstrated its effectiveness and efficiency, the accuracy rate of strategy recommendations can reach about 90%.},
