  abstract={IEC 61499 and Big Data systems, which are also distributed architecture, but they belong to two independent and unrelated platforms due to different network and control concepts. With the development of intelligent manufacturing factories, the big data generated by the process of industrial production is facing unprecedented challenges of storage and data processing. The current approach is to put industrial big data on cloud computing and the industrial automation control program on the side that is close to physical equipment. This architecture has the problems of low efficiency, insufficient security and poor real-time performance. The purpose of this paper is to design an architecture for intergration IEC61499 and Big Data. It can not only reduce the cost of building a smart factory, but also increase the security and data access velocity. More importantly, it can meet the real-time performance of industrial control.},
